      "source": [
        "We used an Isolation Forest as our first model, and the Silhouette Score to evaluate model performance for different parameters.\n",
        "\n",
        "Given that there is no label, we are just trying to find transactions that are anomalies.\n",
        "\n",
        "To find the best parameters I located at different: n_estimators, samples, contamination, max features, and bootstrap method. However, there are quite a few combinations. Hence, I used random sampling of the parameters with a total of 50 iterations. We use the model with best Silhouette score.\n",
        "\n",
        "However, some things to note. I am not sure if contamination is a worthy \"hyperparameter\" for tuning. I noticed that as contamination % goes down, the Silhouette score goes up. Which makes intuitevely since we are reducing the outliers in the dataset leading to a more \"fitted\" model."
